<item>
            <title>[FLINK-18149] Taskmanager logs could not show up in native K8s deployment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-18149</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-17935&quot; title=&quot;Logs could not show up when deploying Flink on Yarn via &amp;quot;--executor&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-17935&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-17935&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we use &lt;tt&gt;flinkConfig.get(DeploymentOptionsInternal.CONF_DIR)&lt;/tt&gt; to replace &lt;tt&gt;CliFrontend.getConfigurationDirectoryFromEnv&lt;/tt&gt;. It will cause problem in native K8s integration. The root cause we set the &lt;tt&gt;DeploymentOptionsInternal.CONF_DIR&lt;/tt&gt; in flink-conf.yaml to a local path. However, it does not exist in JobManager pod.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
